userStories.notes:
Files:
- plugins/confluence/src/index.ts (add configSchema property and ConfigSchema import)
- plugins/confluence/package.json (add configSchema to opentabs field)

Context:
Confluence has both SaaS (atlassian.net/wiki) and self-hosted (Confluence Server/Data Center) deployments. The plugin currently only supports the SaaS domain.

Current code in plugins/confluence/src/index.ts:
```
import type { ToolDefinition } from '@opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk';
...
class ConfluencePlugin extends OpenTabsPlugin {
  readonly name = 'confluence';
  readonly description = 'OpenTabs plugin for Confluence';
  override readonly displayName = 'Confluence';
  readonly urlPatterns = ['*://*.atlassian.net/wiki/*'];
```

Changes:

1. In plugins/confluence/src/index.ts:
   - Change `import type { ToolDefinition } from '@opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk';` to `import type { ConfigSchema, ToolDefinition } from '@opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk';`
   - Add after `readonly urlPatterns = ['*://*.atlassian.net/wiki/*'];`:
     ```
     override readonly configSchema: ConfigSchema = {
       instanceUrl: {
         type: 'url' as const,
         label: 'Confluence URL',
         description: 'The URL of your self-hosted Confluence instance (e.g., https://confluence.example.com). Leave empty to use Confluence Cloud on atlassian.net.',
         required: false,
         placeholder: 'https://confluence.example.com',
       },
     };
     ```

2. In plugins/confluence/package.json, add to `opentabs` object:
   ```json
   "configSchema": {
     "instanceUrl": {
       "type": "url",
       "label": "Confluence URL",
       "description": "The URL of your self-hosted Confluence instance (e.g., https://confluence.example.com). Leave empty to use Confluence Cloud on atlassian.net.",
       "required": false,
       "placeholder": "https://confluence.example.com"
     }
   }
   ```

Constraints:
- Do NOT remove or change existing urlPatterns
- Do NOT set required: true
- Do NOT modify tool files, API files, or isReady logic
